        <h2>Video walkthrough (30-second review)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>0–5s: show locator map from Sprint 16</li>
          <li>5–10s: run element typing and open <code>element-type-map.json</code></li>
          <li>10–15s: generate primitive methods and show <code>action-method-candidates.json</code></li>
          <li>15–20s: generate composites and show <code>composite-action-candidates.json</code></li>
          <li>20–25s: highlight <code>loginAs</code> candidate</li>
          <li>25–30s: show generated page-object method output</li>
        </ul>
      </section> -->

      <section id="ops" class="card">
        <h2>Operational value</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Reduces boilerplate in page-object construction.</li>
          <li>Builds a safer bridge between discovery and generation.</li>
          <li>Preserves human review when confidence is weak.</li>
          <li>Creates reusable artifacts for later test-skeleton generation.</li>
          <li>Supports controlled intelligence instead of unbounded code synthesis.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <div>Runbook 16.5 • QA ALIGN</div>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>